{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "This aligns with the statement by (Gregg, 1984) that the Monitor Hypothesis is one of the five hypotheses developed by Stephen Krashen to explain second language acquisition.",
    "It asserts that the learned system by learners acts as a monitor for what they produce.",
    "Before learners produce speech, they check it with their minds for errors and use the learned system to correct any mentioned errors.",
    "Self-correction occurs when learners use the Monitor to fix sentences after they are produced.",
    "According to this hypothesis, such self-monitoring and self-correction are the only functions of conscious language learning."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "This aligns with the statement by (Gregg, 1984) that the Monitor Hypothesis is one of the five hypotheses developed by Stephen Krashen to explain second language acquisition."
  ]
}